		{
			description: [
				"This dead fish has come back from the dead and now swims around wrecked ships underwater or chases after people in boats. "
				""
				"It does not like people in boats because one day, this fish was caught and eaten alive on a boat, then thrown into a trash can. The people on the boat poured the trash can overboard, polluting the water."
				""
				"The pure rage of seeing these people pollute the water made this fish come back from the dead to attack anyone on a boat. Or at least that's my best guess as to why it doesn't like boats."
				""
				"If you kill this fish, it has a 1% chance to drop a hat with beer. It got this hat from the trash it was thrown out in, which was full of empty beer cans. "
				""
				"Additionally, if you kill it, there is a 5% chance of getting its skull, which is a crazy fast one-handed weapon with 4 attack speed and deals 4.5 damage per hit, making it better than even some enchanted two-handed diamond weapons."
			]
			id: "0102F0C19CA15387"
			invisible: true
			tasks: [{
				icon: {
					Count: 1
					id: "alexsmobs:tab_icon"
					tag: {
						DisplayEntityType: "alexsmobs:skelewag"
					}
				}
				id: "6C1BEBFA5B476D12"
				observe_type: 5
				timer: 0L
				title: "Skelewag"
				to_observe: "alexsmobs:skelewag"
				type: "observation"
			}]
			x: -3.0d
			y: 2.0d
		}
		{
			description: [
				"These money-hungry crabs are a bit like New Yorkers. If you get too close, they will punch you in the face."
				""
				"If you start playing some sick beats, they’ll begin to dance and show off their superior moves. If you kill these chill guys minding their own business, they will drop their legs, which can be cooked into delicious meals like some rangoons or a non-descript tropical stew."
				""
				"Additionally, they may drop their shell, which can be brewed into a potion of knockback resistance. Now that I think about it, these guys aren't so similar to New Yorkers."
			]
			id: "41ED84922099262C"
			invisible: true
			tasks: [{
				icon: {
					Count: 1
					id: "alexsmobs:tab_icon"
					tag: {
