		{
			description: [
				"These ultra-thick pipe cleaners swim around in rivers, jungles, or wetland biomes like mangroves and are always stressed out. To mitigate their stress, they will target living beings to let out some of that tension, much like a stress ball. However, after they de-stress, they often end up hungry and will eat their \"stress ball.\""
				""
				"If they consume three \"stress balls,\" they will become fat and outgrow their old skin and shed it for a new one. With their shed skin, you can make a vine lasso, which is essentially a lead that can be used on all entities, including falling sand and dragons."
			]
			id: "213DBADFDB075999"
			invisible: true
			tasks: [{
				icon: {
					Count: 1
					id: "alexsmobs:tab_icon"
